{
  "bio": [
    "Farhad Moshiri is a business partner of Russian billionaire Usmanov, whom he met in the early 1990s.",
    "An accountant by training, Moshiri once worked for such firms as Ernst & Young and Deloitte Touche.",
    "Alongside Usmanov, he has stakes in Russian mining and steel manufacturing giant Metalloinvest and Russian wireless operator Megafon.",
    "He sold a stake in London's Arsenal soccer club back to Usmanov in 2016 to fund his investment in another English club, Everton, selling the team to billionaire Dan Friedken in 2024 for about $625 million."
  ],
